<subSubSection id="C301DEC5FFD55160FF44208C53C0AC0C" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BA48D4EFFD55160FF44208C53C0AC0C" blockId="0.[136,1452,1430,2066]" pageId="0" pageNumber="215">
<emphasis id="B96F515CFFD55160FF44208C5671AFC4" bold="true" box="[189,308,1502,1526]" pageId="0" pageNumber="215">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C1BF6CDFFD55160FEB6208C5510AFC4" authorityName="T. S. Liu &amp; N. J. Chung ex T. C. Hsu &amp; S. W. Chung" authorityYear="2022" box="[335,597,1502,1526]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sedum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="triangulisepalum">
<emphasis id="B96F515CFFD55160FEB6208C5510AFC4" box="[335,597,1502,1526]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="215">Sedum triangulisepalum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C1BF6CDFFD55160FD13208C5273AFC4" authority="T. S. Liu &amp; N. J. Chung (1977: 23)" authorityName="T. S. Liu &amp; N. J. Chung" authorityPageNumber="23" authorityYear="1977" box="[746,1334,1502,1526]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sedum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="truncatistigmum">
<emphasis id="B96F515CFFD55160FD13208C54F2AFC4" box="[746,951,1502,1526]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="215">S. truncatistigmum</emphasis>
T.S. Liu &amp; N.J. Chung (1977: 23)
</taxonomicName>
in sharing epiphytic life-form, alternate and ±flattened leaves and fused calyx, while the former is readily distinguished in having longer calyx (1.5–2.0 vs. 0.8–1.0 mm) that are only fused at the base (vs. nearly entirely fused).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
