</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C301DEC5FFD55160FF4423E45575AD24" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BA48D4EFFD55160FF4423E45575AD24" blockId="0.[136,1452,1430,2066]" pageId="0" pageNumber="215">
<emphasis id="B96F515CFFD55160FF4423E45698ACFC" bold="true" box="[189,477,1718,1742]" pageId="0" pageNumber="215">Distribution and ecology:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="4C1BF6CDFFD55160FE0E23E455BFACFC" authorityName="T. S. Liu &amp; N. J. Chung ex T. C. Hsu &amp; S. W. Chung" authorityYear="2022" box="[503,762,1718,1742]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sedum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="triangulisepalum">
<emphasis id="B96F515CFFD55160FE0E23E455BFACFC" box="[503,762,1718,1742]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="215">Sedum triangulisepalum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is endemic in 
<collectingCountry id="F30CCDDEFFD55160FC6823E454A7ACFC" box="[913,994,1718,1742]" name="Taiwan" pageId="0" pageNumber="215">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, where it occurs in the northern and eastern portions of the main island and usually grows on tree trunks in montane cloud forests at 
<quantity id="4CE320ABFFD55160FBB023885394ACC3" box="[1097,1233,1754,1778]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.25" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="0.5" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" unit="m" value="1250.0" valueMax="2000.0" valueMin="500.0">500–2000 m</quantity>
elev. (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8AF0BFFFD55160FAE023885785AD24" author="Liu, T. S. &amp; Chung, N. J." pageId="0" pageNumber="215" pagination="10 - 24" refId="ref1496" refString="Liu, T. S. &amp; Chung, N. J. (1977) Crassulaceae. In: Li, H. L., Liu, T. S., Huang, T. C., Koyama, T. &amp; DeVol, C. E. (Eds.) Flora of Taiwan, vol. 3. Epoch Publishing, Taipei, pp. 10 - 24." type="book chapter" year="1977">Liu &amp; Chung 1977</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8AF0BFFFD55160FF3223AC563AAD24" author="Chen, C. H. &amp; Wu, S. C. &amp; Liao, H. C. &amp; Lin, C. Y. &amp; Yeh, H. Y. &amp; Chung, S. W." box="[203,383,1790,1814]" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" refId="ref1198" refString="Chen, C. H., Wu, S. C., Liao, H. C., Lin, C. Y., Yeh, H. Y. &amp; Chung, S. W. (2017) Illustrated Flora of Taiwan, vol. 3. Gramineae - Stellariaceae. Owl Publishing House, Taipei, 416 pp. [In Chinese]" type="book" year="2017">
Chen 
<emphasis id="B96F515CFFD55160FEF323AD5605AD24" box="[266,320,1790,1814]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="215">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8AF0BFFFD55160FE7323AC5561AD24" author="Ito, T. &amp; Yu, C. C. &amp; Nakamura, K &amp; Chung, K. F. &amp; Yang, Q. E. &amp; Fu, C. X. &amp; Qi, Z. C. &amp; Kokubugata, G." box="[394,548,1790,1814]" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" pagination="9 - 22" refId="ref1297" refString="Ito, T., Yu, C. C., Nakamura, K, Chung, K. F., Yang, Q. E., Fu, C. X., Qi, Z. C. &amp; Kokubugata, G. (2017) Unique parallel radiations of highmountainous species of the genus Sedum (Crassulaceae) on the continental island of Taiwan. Molecular Phylogenetic and Evolution 113: 9 - 22. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2017.03.028" type="journal article" year="2017">
Ito 
<emphasis id="B96F515CFFD55160FE5723AD56A1AD24" box="[430,484,1790,1814]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="215">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C301DEC5FFD55160FF4422705434ADB0" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BA48D4EFFD55160FF4422705434ADB0" blockId="0.[136,1452,1430,2066]" pageId="0" pageNumber="215">
<emphasis id="B96F515CFFD55160FF4422705604AD08" bold="true" box="[189,321,1826,1850]" pageId="0" pageNumber="215">Etymology:</emphasis>
—The specific epithet is composed of two Latin elements: 
<emphasis id="B96F515CFFD55160FC252270530FAD08" box="[988,1098,1826,1850]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="215">triangulus</emphasis>
, triangular, and 
<emphasis id="B96F515CFFD55160FAFD22705218AD08" box="[1284,1373,1826,1850]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="215">sepalum</emphasis>
, sepal, referring to its triangular calyx lobes. It should be spelt as “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C1BF6CDFFD55160FCF622145480AD6C" authorityName="T. S. Liu &amp; N. J. Chung ex T. C. Hsu &amp; S. W. Chung" authorityYear="2022" box="[783,965,1862,1886]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sedum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="triangulisepalum">
<emphasis id="B96F515CFFD55160FCF622145480AD6C" box="[783,965,1862,1886]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="215">triangulisepalum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” instead of “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C1BF6CDFFD55160FBAF22145257AD6C" authorityName="Liu &amp; Chung" authorityYear="1977" box="[1110,1298,1862,1886]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sedum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="triangulosepalum">
<emphasis id="B96F515CFFD55160FBAF22145257AD6C" box="[1110,1298,1862,1886]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="215">triangulosepalum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” as originally published by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8AF0BFFFD55160FEE1223856B1ADB0" author="Liu, T. S. &amp; Chung, N. J." box="[280,500,1898,1922]" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" pagination="10 - 24" refId="ref1496" refString="Liu, T. S. &amp; Chung, N. J. (1977) Crassulaceae. In: Li, H. L., Liu, T. S., Huang, T. C., Koyama, T. &amp; DeVol, C. E. (Eds.) Flora of Taiwan, vol. 3. Epoch Publishing, Taipei, pp. 10 - 24." type="book chapter" year="1977">Liu &amp; Chung (1977)</bibRefCitation>
according to Art. 60.10 of the ICN.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C301DEC5FFD55161FF4422DC5418AB11" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="216" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BA48D4EFFD55161FF4422DC5418AB11" blockId="0.[136,1452,1430,2066]" lastBlockId="1.[136,1452,159,291]" lastPageId="1" lastPageNumber="216" pageId="0" pageNumber="215">
<emphasis id="B96F515CFFD55160FF4422DC57B9AD94" bold="true" box="[189,252,1934,1958]" pageId="0" pageNumber="215">Note:</emphasis>
—Two gatherings, “ 
<emphasis id="B96F515CFFD55160FE2022DC5508AD94" box="[473,589,1934,1958]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="215">Suzuki s.n.</emphasis>
” collected from Wulai and “ 
<emphasis id="B96F515CFFD55160FC7522DC5354AD94" box="[908,1041,1934,1958]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="215">Chuang 280</emphasis>
” collected from Lomawanshan, were cited under 
<taxonomicName id="4C1BF6CDFFD55160FEFC22E0554DADF8" authorityName="T. S. Liu &amp; N. J. Chung ex T. C. Hsu &amp; S. W. Chung" authorityYear="2022" box="[261,520,1970,1994]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Crassulaceae" genus="Sedum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="triangulisepalum">
<emphasis id="B96F515CFFD55160FEFC22E0554DADF8" box="[261,520,1970,1994]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="215">Sedum triangulisepalum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF8AF0BFFFD55160FDD622E05449ADF8" author="Liu, T. S. &amp; Chung, N. J." box="[559,780,1970,1994]" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" pagination="10 - 24" refId="ref1496" refString="Liu, T. S. &amp; Chung, N. J. (1977) Crassulaceae. In: Li, H. L., Liu, T. S., Huang, T. C., Koyama, T. &amp; DeVol, C. E. (Eds.) Flora of Taiwan, vol. 3. Epoch Publishing, Taipei, pp. 10 - 24." type="book chapter" year="1977">Liu &amp; Chung (1977)</bibRefCitation>
, and “ 
<emphasis id="B96F515CFFD55160FCB622E05494ADF8" box="[847,977,1970,1994]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="215">Chuang 280</emphasis>
” is presumably a typo of “ 
<emphasis id="B96F515CFFD55160FB1422E05226ADF8" box="[1261,1379,1970,1994]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="215">Chung 280</emphasis>
” since the “ 
<emphasis id="B96F515CFFD55160FF442285562CADDC" box="[189,361,2006,2030]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="215">
<collectorName id="26EEE898FFD55160FF442285567DADDC" box="[189,312,2006,2030]" pageId="0" pageNumber="215">N.J. Chung</collectorName>
280
</emphasis>
” gathering, collected by the second original author and currently preserved in NTUF, matches well with the data given in the original publication (
<bibRefCitation id="EF8AF0BFFFD55160FD7922A85415A220" author="Liu, T. S. &amp; Chung, N. J." box="[640,848,2042,2066]" pageId="0" pageNumber="215" pagination="10 - 24" refId="ref1496" refString="Liu, T. S. &amp; Chung, N. J. (1977) Crassulaceae. In: Li, H. L., Liu, T. S., Huang, T. C., Koyama, T. &amp; DeVol, C. E. (Eds.) Flora of Taiwan, vol. 3. Epoch Publishing, Taipei, pp. 10 - 24." type="book chapter" year="1977">Liu &amp; Chung 1977</bibRefCitation>
). There are nine duplicates of 
<emphasis id="B96F515CFFD55160FB6C22A8524EA220" box="[1173,1291,2042,2066]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="215">Chung 280</emphasis>
, including one (barcode: F00008307) labelled as “ 
<typeStatus id="54A033ECFFD45161FDF225CD5528AA85" box="[523,621,159,183]" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">holotype</typeStatus>
” and the others (barcodes: F00008308–F00008315) as “isotype”. 
<location id="8EC4DB95FFD45161FABE25CD52E9AA85" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:03B23C58FFD55161FF7121B35418AB11:8EC4DB95FFD45161FABE25CD52E9AA85" box="[1351,1452,159,183]" country="Taiwan" municipality="Images" name="Although" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">Although</location>
these labels could not be archived as the legitimate designation of types as they are not effectively published (see Art. 7.10 of the ICN), they supposedly reflect the original author’s intention and are thus adopted here. 
<collectingMunicipality id="6BC01734FFD45161FBA325BA53E2AB32" box="[1114,1191,232,256]" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">Images</collectingMunicipality>
of all type materials are available in the “Plants of 
<collectingCountry id="F30CCDDEFFD45161FE5B245956B6AB11" box="[418,499,267,291]" name="Taiwan" pageId="1" pageNumber="216">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
” database [http://tai2.ntu.edu.tw].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
</treatment>
